https://github.com/Dolibarr/dolibarr/blob/e5da68b3bd8101af8742a96dd578ecbfcc9a1ce1/htdocs/fourn/facture/paiement.php#L618-L722

We have 
```
$alreadypayed = price2num($paiement + $creditnotes + $deposits, 'MT'); 
```
Which is never used again.

Should the ending be:

```php
if ($paiement) { 
 	print '+'.price($paiement); 
 }
if ($creditnotes) { 
 	print '+'.price($creditnotes); 
 } 
 if ($deposits) { 
 	print '+'.price($deposits); 
 }
```

??

Even though I don't thing it looks good, you culd end up in a column like:
`0.00+152.36+552.20`

I would do a tooltip when hovering over the already paid amount.

```php
//print '<td class="right">'.price($sign * $objp->am);
print '<td class="right">';
print '<span style="'.( $alreadypayed ? 'border-bottom: 1px dotted #000;' : '').'" class="classfortooltip" data-title="';
if ($paiement) {
	$tooltip .= "<strong>".$langs->trans("Payments")."</strong>: ".price($paiement)."<br>";
}
if ($creditnotes) {
	$tooltip .= "<strong>".$langs->trans("CreditNotes")."</strong>: ".price($creditnotes)."<br>";
}
if ($deposits) {
	$tooltip .= "<strong>".$langs->trans("Deposits")."</strong>: ".price($deposits)."<br>";
}
print dol_escape_htmltag($tooltip);
print '">';
print price($sign * $alreadypayed);
print '</span>';
print '</td>';
```

Also changed `$objp->am` for `$alreadypayed`

